# Copy to `.env` in this folder. Vite exposes only vars prefixed with VITE_.

# API base (no trailing slash).
#
# Dev (`npm run dev`): the app always calls same-origin `/api`. Vite reads this
# variable and proxies `/api` → this URL (see vite.config.js). Restart dev after changes.
# Example remote API:
#   VITE_API_URL=https://smb-financial-api.fly.dev
# Local backend (default if unset):
#   VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
#
# Production build: `vite build` inlines VITE_API_URL for direct calls (no proxy).

# Production: set VITE_API_URL to your public API origin (no trailing slash).
# Netlify: also set in Site settings → Environment variables, or see repo root netlify.toml [build.environment].
# Example Fly.io: https://your-app.fly.dev
